cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the extension of lambda calculus with non-injective pattern matching interpreted using relations, which is a topic closely related to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the semantics of the language using "ideal relations" between partial orders, which is a topic in logic and set theory (cs.LO). The second semantics discussed in the paper is motivated by its potential use with separation algebra, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions pointfree relation calculi, which is a topic in functional programming (cs.FL), and refinement calculi, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
